race.comment: CALIDO MAGIC (2) wasn't the best away and settled well back before launching late to get up for fourth last time out in a 1000m Randwick Highway. Big drop in grade today and looks well in after Owen's claim. Sure to give a good account. YOUNG MISTER GRACE (6) went around at prohibitive odds and never looked in doubt on debut over 1000m here recently. Powered through the line that day so another 100m looks ideal. Draws the paint and can win again. CAESAR (7) has not been produced since a tough win over this distance on debut at Gosford in July. Trialling well for Peter Snowden and looks ready for a positive return. LADY SHENANIGANS (4) was disappointing here at this trip last start after a win in a similar contest the run prior. Can win if she brings her A-game. Doubt the other two runners can land a blow.
